urlText: Trackwork Coaches replace the XPT service between Albury and Melbourne
content:
Rail network manager ARTC has implemented speed restrictions on the North East Rail Lines in Victoria. 
To maintain service times and connections with other services the Sydney to Melbourne, Melbourne to Sydney XPT train service has been replaced by road coaches to/from Albury and Melbourne. 

CLK624 coaches will depart Melbourne at the amended departure time of 07:00hrs
CLK622 coaches will depart Melbourne at the amended departure time of 18:30hrs.
subtitle: Trackwork Coaches replace the XPT service between Albury and Melbourne

urlText: Trackwork between Tallawong and Epping
content:
Saturday 9 and Sunday 10 May
  • Buses replace Metro services between Tallawong and Epping.
  • Metro services run between Epping and Chatswood only.
  • Trackwork on the City Circle may also affect how you travel.
  • T1 North Shore Line trains run between Berowra and Wynyard, and T9 Northern Line trains run between Hornsby and Central only.
  • If you are travelling to or from the City you may need to change trains at Wynyard or Central to continue your journey.
  • Plan your trip before you travel for up-to-date information.
Bus routes
12M: Tallawong, then all stations to Epping and return

urlText: Trackwork between East Hills and Sydenham or Central
content:
Monday 4 to Thursday 7 May
  • Nightly from 10.10pm until 2am, buses replace trains between East Hills and Sydenham.
  • Trains run between Macarthur and East Hills, and between Wolli Creek and the City via the Airport, some to a changed timetable. 
  • If you are travelling from the City to stations Turrella to East Hills catch a T3 Bankstown or T4 Illawarra Line train to Sydenham and change for a bus.
  • Nightly from 10.50pm until 2am, buses also replace trains between Sydenham and Central via the Airport.
  • Trains run between Macarthur and East Hills, some to a changed timetable. 
  • Plan your trip before you travel for up-to-date information.
Bus routes

13T8: East Hills, then all stations to Padstow, then Sydenham and return

subtitle: Trackwork between East Hills and Sydenham or Central

    Nightly from 10 50 p m until 2 a m, buses also replace trains between Sydenham and Central via the Airport.
    Trains run between Macarthur and East Hills, some to a changed timetable.

urlText: Buses replace all L1 Dulwich Hill Line light rail services daily
content:
On Saturday 16 and Sunday 17 May
From 6am to 11pm
  • Buses replace all L1 Dulwich Hill Line light rail services daily between Central Grand Concourse and Dulwich Hill in both directions, to allow for maintenance work.
Replacement buses will operate on the following frequency:
  • From 6am to 10am – 15 to 20 minute frequency
  • From 10am to 5pm – 10 to 15 minute frequency
  • From 5pm to 11pm – 15 to 20 minute frequency
Please allow extra travel time and follow the yellow directional signs to the nearby replacement bus stop locations.

Buses will not stop at the following locations:
  • Capitol Square (towards Central and Dulwich Hill) - Please use the alternative stop at Central Grand Concourse (approx. 5 minute walk)
  • Exhibition Centre (towards Dulwich Hill) – Please use the alternative stop at Convention (approx. 5 minute walk)
  • Pyrmont Bay (towards Central and Dulwich Hill) – Please use the alternative stop at The Star (approx. 5 minute walk)
Normal light rail services will resume 6am Monday 18 May.
subtitle: Buses replace all L1 Dulwich Hill Line light rail services daily
